IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Kings Daughters mission is to provide support to CHKD through fundraising, volunteerism, leadership AND advocacy for children IN SOUTHEASTERN VA AND NORTH EASTERN NC.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE KING'S DAUGHTERS MISSION IS TO PROVIDE SUPPORT TO CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL OF THE KING'S DAUGHTERS THROUGH FUNDRAISING, VOLUNTEERISM, LEADERSHIP AND ADVOCACY FOR THE CHILDREN OF SOUTHEASTERN VIRGINIA AND NORTHEASTERN NORTH CAROLINA.
IRS990.Desc: THE KING'S DAUGHTERS, FOUNDING ORGANIZATION OF CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL OF THE KING'S DAUGHTERS (CHKD), HAS A LEGACY OF SERVICE TO THE HOSPITAL, FUNDING CRUCIAL NEEDS SUCH AS NURSING EDUCATION, THE CHILD ABUSE PROGRAM AND THE PURCHASE OF MUCH-NEEDED EQUIPMENT THROUGH CONTRIBUTIONS AND GRANTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization monitors the use of donated funds by having a representative of the recipient organization report at board meetings on a regular basis. Expenditures of grants are open to review by the Organization upon request.
GOVERNING DOCUMENTS INCLUDING THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC THROUGH DIRECT INQUIRY AND REQUEST.

THE ORGANIZATION IS COMPRISED OF VOLUNTEER GROUPS, CALLED 'CIRCLES' WITH A COMBINED MEMBERSHIP OF 1,075 THROUGHOUT THE HAMPTON ROADS AREA. THESE DEDICATED VOLUNTEERS RAISE FRIENDS FUNDS AND AWARENESS FOR CHKD THROUGH CIRCLE PROJECTS, CANISTERS, AND MAJOR FUNDRAISING EVENTS E.G. RUNWALK FOR THE KIDS, MOONLIGHT & MISTLETOE, AND BREAKFAST WITH SANTA. CIRCLE MEMBERS ALSO MAKE ITEMS FOR CHKD SUCH AS NEONATAL CAPS AND BOOTIES, AND TEDDY BEARS, AS WELL AS PROVIDING IN-HOSPITAL VOLUNTEERS. CHKD RELIES ON THE KING'S DAUGHTERS MORE THAN EVER TO MEET THE BURGEONING MEDICAL NEEDS OF THE REGION'S CHILDREN. ANYONE CAN SUPPORT THE KING'S DAUGHTERS TODAY BY VOLUNTEERING, JOINING A CIRCLE, OR ATTENDING OUR EVENTS. VISIT US AT WWW.KINGSDAUGHTERS.ORG FOR MORE INFORMATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FILING ORGANIZATION HAS NO EMPLOYEES BUT REIMBURSES ANOTHER ENTITY FOR CERTAIN ADMINISTRATIVE SERVICES. THEREFORE, THE FILING ORGANIZATION FILES NO W-2S BECAUSE IT DOES NOT EMPLOY ANY INDIVIDUALS.

6. NORFOLK CITY UNION OF THE KING'S DAUGHTERS, INC. IS A VIRGINIA NON-STOCK CORPORATION. AS A VIRGINIA NON-STOCK CORPORATION, IT HAS MEMBERS. THERE ARE THREE CATEGORIES OF MEMBERS: ADULT MEMBERS, JUNIOR MEMBERS AND HONORARY MEMBERS. 7A. ADULT MEMBERS ELECT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE ORGANIZATION. 7B. THE AMENDMENT OF THE BYLAWS OF THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES THE APPROVAL OF A MAJORITY OF THE ADULT MEMBERS.

THE 990 IS PREPARED USING THE ANNUAL TRIAL BALANCE THAT IS REGULARLY REVIEWED BY THE BOARD. THE INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM, KPMG, SERVED AS THE PAID PREPARER AND WORKED CLOSELY WITH THE ORGANIZATION TO PREPARE THE FORM 990. UPON COMPLETION OF THE DRAFT OF THE RETURN, THE BOARD WILL MEET TO REVIEW FOR ACCURACY AND COMPLETENESS. AFTER APPROVAL, THE FORM IS FINALIZED FOR RELEASE.

CONFLICT OF INTEREST QUESTIONNAIRES ARE SENT OUT AND COMPLETED BY BOARD MEMBERS ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. THEY ARE REGULARLY UPDATED FOR ANY CHANGES AND REVIEWED FOR ANY ISSUES THAT MAY IMPAIR A MEMBER'S INDEPENDENCE. IN THE EVENT OF ANY CONFLICTS, THE BOARD MEMBER WILL BE EXCUSED FROM ANY DECISIONS INVOLVING THE CONFLICTING PARTY.

THE ORGANIZATION'S PRESIDENT AND OTHER OFFICERS SERVE IN A VOLUNTEER CAPACITY AND DO NOT RECEIVE COMPENSATION. AS SUCH THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT CURRENTLY HAVE A PROCESS FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR THE PRESIDENT AND OTHER OFFICERS. ANY STAFF OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE EMPLOYEES OF AND ARE COMPENSATED BY CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL OF THE KING'S DAUGHTERS (CHKD), AN AFFILIATED ORGANIZATION. THESE STAFF ARE SUBJECT TO CHKD'S COMPENSATION POLICIES AND PROCESSES. CHKD IS THEN REIMBURSED BY THE ORGANIZATION FOR COMPENSATION PAID.
GOVERNING DOCUMENTS INCLUDING THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC THROUGH DIRECT INQUIRY AND REQUEST.
